    "Then Nahash the Ammonite came up, and encamped against Jabeshgilead: and all the men of Jabesh said unto Nahash, Make a covenant with us, and we will serve thee.",
    "And Nahash the Ammonite answered them, <span class=\"place\">On</span> this condition will I make a covenant with you, that I may thrust out all your right eyes, and lay it for a reproach upon all <span class=\"place\">Israel</span>.",
    "And the elders of Jabesh said unto him, Give us seven days' respite, that we may send messengers unto all the coasts of <span class=\"place\">Israel</span>: and then, if there be no man to save us, we will come out to thee.",
    "Then came the messengers to Gibeah of <span class=\"person\">Saul</span>, and told the tidings in the ears of the people: and all the people lifted up their voices, and wept.",
